Use these rules to keep frontend work consistent for future prompts and implementation.

---

## 1) Framework & Structure

- **Next.js 16.x** with App Router.
- TypeScript only.
- Organize by feature (e.g., `app/(admin)/loans`, `app/(admin)/billing`).
- Next.js 16 requires convention of proxy instead of middleware files.

---

## 2) UI System

- **Use ShadCN UI components** wherever possible.
- Use **sonner** (ShadCN) for notifications and toasts.
- Modularize UI into reusable components:
    - `components/ui` for shared primitives
    - `components/features/<feature>` for domain-specific UI
- Refer to @brand.md for branding guide

---

## 3) Theming & Typography

- Dark theme by default.
- Use **Rethink Sans** for headings.
- Use **Inter** for body.
- Orange gradient highlights (per branding guide).

---

## 4) UX Guidelines

- Prefer simple admin-first workflows.
- Use wizards for loan creation.
- Always show tenant context and billing status.
- Provide clear audit log visibility.

---

## 5) Forms & Validation

- Use schema-based validation (e.g., Zod).
- Show inline validation with consistent error messaging.
- Keep inputs accessible and keyboard-friendly.

---

## 6) Date, Time & Number Formatting

All date/time and number formatting uses utilities from `lib/utils.ts`.

### Timezone

- Database stores all dates in **UTC**.
- Frontend displays in **Malaysia timezone (GMT+8)** using `date-fns-tz`.
- Use `toMalaysiaTime()` when converting UTC dates for display.

### Date/Time Utilities

| Function | Output Example | Use Case |
|----------|----------------|----------|
| `formatDate(date)` | "30 Jan 2026" | General date display |
| `formatDateTime(date)` | "30 Jan 2026, 2:30 PM" | Full date + time |
| `formatTime(date)` | "2:30 PM" | Time only |
| `formatRelativeTime(date)` | "5 minutes ago" | Recent activity, login logs |
| `formatSmartDateTime(date)` | Relative if <24h, else full | Audit logs, notifications |
| `formatDateForInput(date)` | "2026-01-30" | Form date inputs |

### Currency & Number Formatting

| Function | Output Example | Use Case |
|----------|----------------|----------|
| `formatCurrency(amount)` | "RM 1,234.56" | Money display |
| `formatNumber(amount, decimals)` | "1,234.56" | Numbers without currency |

### Safe Math Utilities

JavaScript floating-point arithmetic causes precision issues (e.g., `0.1 + 0.2 = 0.30000000000000004`). Always use these utilities for financial calculations:

| Function | Description | Example |
|----------|-------------|---------|
| `safeRound(value, decimals)` | Round to decimal places | `safeRound(10.456, 2)` → `10.46` |
| `safeAdd(...values)` | Add multiple numbers safely | `safeAdd(0.1, 0.2)` → `0.3` |
| `safeSubtract(initial, ...values)` | Subtract numbers safely | `safeSubtract(100, 30, 20)` → `50` |
| `safeMultiply(a, b, decimals)` | Multiply safely | `safeMultiply(10.5, 3)` → `31.5` |
| `safeDivide(a, b, decimals)` | Divide safely (0 if divisor is 0) | `safeDivide(100, 3)` → `33.33` |
| `safePercentage(part, total)` | Calculate percentage | `safePercentage(25, 100)` → `25` |
| `toSafeNumber(value)` | Convert string/null to number | `toSafeNumber("123.45")` → `123.45` |

### Best Practices

- Always use these utilities; never format dates/numbers inline.
- For user-facing timestamps, prefer `formatRelativeTime()` for recent events.
- Hover/title attributes can show full date when using relative time.
- **Never use raw arithmetic (`+`, `-`, `*`, `/`) for currency calculations.**
- Use `toSafeNumber()` when converting API response strings to numbers.
